title: No truth to story of giant python swallowing Kulim woman - Nation
text:
ALOR SETAR: Police have refuted reports of a woman in Kulim being swallowed by a giant python.
Kulim deputy police chief  Deputy Supt Barudin Wariso when contacted on Friday said there was no truth to the reports and pictures, which have gone viral on social media.
"The pictures and information have been circulating on social media since Thursday.
"If the news was true, it would definitely have rocked the district. Judging from the pictures, it would have been world news and Kulim would be famous internationally," he said.
DSP Barudin advised netizens to be careful and responsible when uploading news on social media.
